Singapore will impose further restrictions on social activities from May 16 to stem the spread of Covid-19. Here are some answers to lingering questions you might have about the new rules:🏫 Will a parent be able to send 3 kids to school?Yes. There will be some flexibility for family members who may need to move in bigger groups to attend classes or go to work in the same vehicle  for instance.Read more:https://str.sg/JvGL🏢 Do I need to return to the office?Work from home will be the default mode. Employers must ensure that employees who are able to work from home do so.🛍Can I still visit shopping malls?Yes. But the occupancy limits for shopping malls will be further reduced from the current limit of 10 sq m per person of gross floor area  to 16 sq m per person.Read more:https://str.sg/JvGb🏸 Can I play badminton or go swimming?Yes. But you must do so in a group of no more than 2 people.🏃Will a family of 4 be allowed to exercise outdoors together?Individuals from the same household can exercise together  but should split into pairs and maintain safe distancing.Read more:https://str.sg/JvGE
